\begin_layout Subsubsection
Gröbner bases
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Maybe the most well-known method to prove geometry theorems algebraically
 is the 
\emph on
Gröbner basis method
\emph default

\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
method!--, Gröbner basis
\end_layout

\end_inset

 introduced by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Kapur1986"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "KutzlerStifter"

\end_inset

.
 Similarly to Wu's method, it usually consists of the following parts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Algebraization of the problem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Analysis of the algebraic equation system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In its basic version it is not capable to provide degeneracy conditions,
 so it will be extended as follows (by improving the algorithm suggested
 by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "RecioVelez99"

\end_inset

, following the idea of Chou's):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Algebraization of the problem.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Turning the equation system into an equivalent system by eliminating dependent
 variables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Reading off the algebraic degeneracy conditions and converting them to geometric
 statements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In both variants Step 2 is computationally heavy for many elementary Euclidean
 geometry theorems.
 In fact, Step 2 is computed by calculating the Gröbner basis of a set of
 multivariate polynomials which is a general method not only for geometry
 theorem proving but to solve a wide range of other mathematical problems.
 When computing a Gröbner basis of a set much more extra information is
 yielded than for Wu's method, thus this technique is theoretically much
 slower for the general case.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the other hand, effective computation of a Gröbner basis has a huge literatur
e and there are remarkable results which promote this method nearly so effective
 like Wu's method is, and has some different advantages and extra features.
 What is more, in classroom situations it usually overperforms the other
 methods.
 Thus in this thesis the focus is on finding acceptable implementations
 to compute Gröbner bases (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chap:Implementation-in-GeoGebra"

\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sub:Computing-Gröbner-bases"

\end_inset

