 of too many steps.
 Even if each step can be understood at elementary or secondary level, the
 high number of steps makes the output not useful in the education.
 Thus it would be desirable to combine atomic steps to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

well visible
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, separatable parts, to reduce the number of steps to help the student to
 get an easier overview of the proof.
 The desirable number of steps is as minimal as possible, and later these
 steps could be refined into more detailed ones on a thorough study.
\end_layout

